Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.64,0:00:08.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief, \Nit's my turn next.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.01,0:00:10.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Saturday night, \Nunder the waning moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.67,0:00:14.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I shall seize the jewel upon the \Nhead of the untarnished nail,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.70,0:00:18.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and thus repay the debt I owe you\N from 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:28.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Long time no see,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.13,0:00:31.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:35.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Unlike then, your partner here \Nisn't worth a damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:36.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.76,0:00:43.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"The Female with 20 Faces" who dropped \Nout of sight in Paris 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.29,0:00:45.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The gentlewoman thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:48.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...the Phantom Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.31,0:00:52.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see! It's not deja vu!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.20,0:00:54.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's the guy from 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.28,0:00:57.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Mom told me this story the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.78,0:01:00.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It all started 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.69,0:01:03.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A Saturday night when the \Nfull moon was bright...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.43,0:01:10.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,See? What'd I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:11.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-What's with the handcuffs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.67,0:01:14.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And no sense having two of you, \Nso you'll disappear for good...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.72,0:01:21.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:28.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.40,0:01:30.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.44,0:01:35.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's just like what Mom was gushing \Nabout, how she and Dad first met!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.32,0:03:12.97,Signs - Thief Title,,0,100,11,,{\a3}{\fad(1000,0)}Phantom Lady and the Ryoma Treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.28,0:03:12.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\a6}So, what are you going to do,\N Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:18.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You can try to escape in \Nthat car like 18 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.78,0:03:23.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,except it was a\N slim motorcycle then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.81,0:03:28.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That car is compact, but not enough to fit \Nthrough the windows of this observation deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.24,0:03:36.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although, being a replica, \Nyou can't drive it in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.91,0:03:37.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.05,0:03:43.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then this entire prized collection is a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:48.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And as for the big-ass ruby coming \Nin next week, it's actually a fake
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:52.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,that you'll say was stolen by Kid,\N and then sell replicas on the black market.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.79,0:03:55.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's all been arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.39,0:03:58.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All I have to do now is take your life
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.01,0:04:00.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and send out our fake Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.77,0:04:03.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.69,0:04:09.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You really think you can take the life...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.40,0:04:10.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...of a phantom thief so easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:16.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:18.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He has nowhere to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.70,0:04:21.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As long as we block the elevator!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.56,0:04:24.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,K-Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.04,0:04:25.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...vanished with the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.86,0:04:27.71,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.29,0:04:32.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That car makes engine noises,\N but it's a fake!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.61,0:04:34.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.03,0:04:37.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You said it should be a \Ndo-over of 18 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.68,0:04:40.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so I went ahead and arranged \Nthings like they were then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:44.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.94,0:04:50.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-He looped around behind us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:51.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.44,0:04:53.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't let him get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.99,0:04:58.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.41,0:05:02.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Shiba Park is... over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:05.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Maybe head-on won't work...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.17,0:05:10.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...but I can get through sideways!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.94,0:05:14.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,D-Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.38,0:05:18.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Let's get out of here \Nbefore the cops come!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.43,0:05:20.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,P-President!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.43,0:05:21.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What are those strange threads?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.66,0:05:33.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The height of Toto Tower's special \Nobservation deck is 250 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.19,0:05:36.95,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,250 = gt squared over 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.95,0:05:42.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Subtract air resistance and that gives us\N about 7.1 seconds 'til impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:45.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Enough time to spring \Nthis cheap handcuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.54,0:05:48.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,One of their shots must've \Nripped a hole in my pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.96,0:05:50.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My lock-picking wire is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:53.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Crap! What do I do?! What do I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.78,0:05:56.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Wire! Wire! Wire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.20,0:05:58.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.39,0:06:01.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Never forget your poker face, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:04.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The hairpin!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.23,0:06:33.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ah, well, at least thanks to the commotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.79,0:06:35.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,those guys will probably \Nend up getting arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.21,0:06:40.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They should be held as snug as bugs \Nfor a while with the thread I set up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.22,0:06:42.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,while circling the car around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.67,0:06:47.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now, what do I do with this happy-go-lucky \Ngirl who slept through all the excitement?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.35,0:06:51.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My dad stole a kiss from my mom when \Nthey were in the same situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.09,0:06:57.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A-Although it's my fault \Nshe got mixed up in this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:02.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-I'll let her have a rain check tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:08.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, come on, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.85,0:07:13.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You should've told me the bad guy from \N18 years ago was never sent to prison!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.00,0:07:15.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\a6}The prosecutor's office is charging \NPresident Gouzu with suspicion of...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.66,0:07:17.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That guy put me through the wringer because \Nhe thought he was getting revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.00,0:07:19.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But you caught him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.68,0:07:21.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Great job...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.54,0:07:23.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...Kid the Phantom Thief II.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.28,0:07:29.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,By the way, Chikage-san, \Nwhen are you coming back to Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.34,0:07:33.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My friend here has really taken a \Nliking to me and won't let me go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:36.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:40.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right. \NPresident Gouzu has apprentices,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.65,0:07:44.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and apparently, they're using the \Nsame methods to line their pockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.90,0:07:49.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A long time ago, I did my best \Nto gather up the evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.34,0:07:54.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but I still never found the place where \Nthey stored all the fake merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.42,0:07:59.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So please teach them a lesson too, \NMagician Under the Moonlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.44,0:08:02.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I already mailed you a list of merchandise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:04.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.02,0:08:05.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-Hey! W-Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.68,0:08:13.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ryoma Sakamoto three-piece memento set?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.68,0:08:13.56,Signs,,0,0,0,,From: Chikage Kuroba\NSub: Ryoma Mementos\NRyoma Sakamoto three-piece memento set\NGun Belt\NHanging Scroll\NSake Cup
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.41,0:08:16.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What a pain in the ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.80,0:08:23.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So this is it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:28.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Why are there so many?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:42.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I think Chikage-sama has already told \Nyou what happened, Young Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.42,0:08:44.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but Phantom Lady,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.36,0:08:50.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,that is, Chikage-sama, didn't steal \Nall these items because she wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.48,0:08:58.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Gouzu sent out a fake notice using her name, \Nclaiming she would steal the Ryoma treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.16,0:09:02.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's pretty much what Mom said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:04.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They were using her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.28,0:09:09.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They knew if they sent out a fake advance notice,\N Phantom Lady would definitely show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.42,0:09:14.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They tricked her into stealing the treasure, \Nthen mass-produced replicas themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:20.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and swindled collectors into buying the fakes \Nby claiming they were the stolen originals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.62,0:09:25.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But Mom could tell the treasures she stole \Nwere fake and kept returning them to the cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.32,0:09:29.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then, 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.20,0:09:32.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...they plotted to wipe out Chikage-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.68,0:09:36.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Except, standing in their way was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.73,0:09:40.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...my old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.88,0:09:44.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Toichi Kuroba, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.05,0:09:48.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.01,0:09:54.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Toichi-sama saved Chikage-sama, then became \NKid the Phantom Thief to protect her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.06,0:10:02.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But it's nearly 20 years later, and their \Ndisciples are using the same means to get rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.67,0:10:08.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's why Mom asked me to \Ncapture them too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.23,0:10:10.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.25,0:10:13.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,To that effect, Chikage-sama has gathered
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.93,0:10:19.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,all of these mass-produced replicas of \NRyoma's treasures from various collectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.13,0:10:22.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.22,0:10:24.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, they're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.59,0:10:28.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now the question is, how do I \Ncatch these guys in the act?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.80,0:10:31.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.87,0:10:33.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.86,0:10:54.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Listen, Kaito, and listen well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.00,0:10:58.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,When the magic's got you stumped, \Nyou can often find a hint
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.02,0:10:59.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,by thinking in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.87,0:11:01.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thinking in reverse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.26,0:11:06.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Magicians always have to \Noutwit their audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.53,0:11:08.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If a certain idea is tripping you up,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.59,0:11:11.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,you should think about an \Nexactly opposite method.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:16.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now {\i1}that{\i0} idea is sure to surprise them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.28,0:11:18.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Do you understand, Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.86,0:11:29.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thinking in reverse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.13,0:11:30.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.88,0:11:33.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.19,0:11:39.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is my one-time chance \Nto expose their misdeeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.01,0:11:40.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll show 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.63,0:11:47.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That Kid the Phantom Thief \Ndoes more than just steal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.78,0:12:05.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's no need to be hasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:07.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I just have to wait for the right day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.08,0:12:12.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's gonna return items that he stole?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:16.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Is that what Kid's advance \Nnotice really said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.91,0:12:17.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.87,0:12:23.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"One day soon, I'm going to show up at \Nthe currently-running Ryoma exhibition
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.25,0:12:25.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,to return three items.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:27.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.33,0:12:29.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-Three items?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.92,0:12:33.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Apparently, Shishihiko Tarumi-san, \Nthe sponsor of the Ryoma exhibition,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.96,0:12:37.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,did the same thing 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.01,0:12:40.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The three items were stolen then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:44.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The letter Ryoma Sakamoto's wife\N wrote him on a scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.66,0:12:48.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,the night before he was assassinated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.06,0:12:53.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,the soy sauce sake cup that became stained \Nwith his blood when he was assassinated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:58.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and the concealed pistol that \NRyoma had on him at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.14,0:13:02.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It was a Smith and Wesson type 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.10,0:13:05.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Look, that's what it says on \Nthe back of the advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.60,0:13:07.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.40,0:13:10.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,e-except Kid isn't the one \Nwho stole them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:15.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the "Female with 20 Faces." \NThe gentlewoman thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:18.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The Phantom Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.49,0:13:23.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the connection was \Nbetween Kid and Lady,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.20,0:13:26.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but after she stole those three items,\N Lady gave up a life of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.93,0:13:30.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you consider that Kid came on \Nthe scene two years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.84,0:13:34.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,it may have been a master \Nand disciple relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.51,0:13:37.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So when is he coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.50,0:13:41.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't know. It just says "one day soon" \Non the advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:46.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then let's cancel the Ryoma exhibition \Nimmediately and get the people out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.78,0:13:51.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He withheld the date and time \Nto put us at a disadvantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.17,0:13:53.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Because he knows that it's easier \Njust to return something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.57,0:13:57.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But, Nakamori-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.26,0:14:00.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's offering to return stolen goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.40,0:14:02.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Why should we reject that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.88,0:14:04.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I know, but Superintendent...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.80,0:14:10.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Besides, to catch Kid, we first \Nneed to invite him in, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.67,0:14:15.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Jirokichi Suzuki, the owner of the Suzuki \NMuseum, received the advance notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.28,0:14:17.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and he agrees with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.51,0:14:21.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He said, "Leave the entrance \Nwide open and the exit narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:25.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Those are the basics of \Ncatching a mouse."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.84,0:14:36.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I said I'd return 'em,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:40.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but how can I bring in \Nall these faux treasures?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.02,0:14:48.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.83,0:14:50.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm on a diet!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.91,0:14:53.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My stomach's starting to get flabby,\N which is like a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:57.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So I go like this and \Ntense my tummy muscles...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.30,0:15:02.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Jeez. I was wondering \Nwhat you were up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.52,0:15:05.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Too bad your tummy's starting to \Nstick out and not your chest, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.96,0:15:08.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.70,0:15:11.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it! You always dodge it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.23,0:15:13.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Aoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.71,0:15:35.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nothing unusual at either \Nthe front or back entrances!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:36.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.86,0:15:37.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.74,0:15:42.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Good job to you too, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:47.39,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ryoma Exhibition
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.00,0:16:13.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is the gun belt Ryoma got\N from Takasugi Shinsaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.37,0:16:15.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.52,0:16:17.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although I'm sure it's a fake...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:21.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But nobody's looking at the treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:23.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess that makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.77,0:16:25.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All of them are focused on...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.93,0:16:31.43,Signs,,0,0,0,,Space reserved for Kid the Phantom Thief \Nto return treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.94,0:16:39.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That Suzuki guy sure knows \Nhow to stir up a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:53.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.37,0:16:56.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Only that space has sensors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.18,0:17:00.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.02,0:17:02.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It was just meant to be a little prank...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.84,0:17:05.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And undercover cops are \Nmixed in with the crowd,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.55,0:17:11.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so they can quickly nab anyone \Nwho seems suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.29,0:17:18.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sorry, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.81,0:17:20.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.65,0:17:31.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.04,0:17:33.95,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.22,0:17:40.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We went to the trouble of coming here, but \Nit looks like Kid-sama may not even show up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.22,0:17:42.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, why don't we go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.05,0:17:47.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Forget it! I'm not leaving until \NI meet my beloved Kid-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.85,0:17:56.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That twerp came here to be \Nthe fly in my ointment again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.85,0:18:04.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Their security is meticulous \Nthis time, Young Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.57,0:18:07.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And I bumped into a real troublemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.24,0:18:12.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.08,0:18:15.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It seems this isn't going to be an easy job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.12,0:18:18.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. The wheels are \Nturning in my head, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.50,0:18:22.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Young Master, do you have a plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.62,0:18:25.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.76,0:18:28.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jii-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.92,0:18:31.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes, Young Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.01,0:18:35.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I think it's about time to hit \N'em with my next advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:37.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:39.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And what's it going to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.64,0:18:42.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I've got something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.66,0:18:46.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A brilliant note befitting this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.68,0:19:02.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,S-Senior Adviser!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.42,0:19:05.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,S-Somebody just dropped this\N in the post box!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.63,0:19:09.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-This is one of \NKid's announcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.63,0:19:10.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.43,0:19:19.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"Tomorrow at 8:00 pm,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.66,0:19:23.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,right before closing, I shall bring \Nover the pistol and other items,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.79,0:19:27.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and by the name of Ryoma Sakamoto, \Npatriot of the Bakumatsu period,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.82,0:19:32.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll give them a good washing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.42,0:19:34.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.42,0:19:36.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.08,0:19:45.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But there's still something \Nfishy about all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.84,0:19:50.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid obviously didn't name the date \Nand time of his appearance this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.06,0:19:52.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so why would he \Nsuddenly choose tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.45,0:19:53.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Just maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.68,0:19:58.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...Kid was waiting for something until today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.10,0:20:03.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.60,0:20:07.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.36,0:20:11.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.13,0:20:15.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.18,0:20:16.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.69,0:20:46.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and rack your brains,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.22,0:20:49.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,you modern-day Sherlock Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.17,0:21:04.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Young Master, as requested, \NI've prepared the props
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.78,0:21:07.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,for your next magic show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.16,0:21:14.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.61,0:21:20.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Young Master, please be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.89,0:21:24.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This time, the police aren't \Nyour only adversaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.80,0:21:27.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.55,0:21:30.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I bet we're gonna have another \Nfun showdown this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:39.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You don't wanna miss this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.66,0:21:44.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The battle between me and my destined \Nrival, the pint-sized brilliant detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.43,0:21:47.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The illusion must go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.33,0:23:24.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I should've figured this job wouldn't be easy,\N since even Mom left it for me to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.60,0:23:29.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And it's made even worse with the involvement \Nof the brilliant munchkin detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.14,0:23:32.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, all of these \Nchallenges get me fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.76,0:23:35.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In the end, I'll pull off a magnificent \Nvictory with the aid of astounding magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.69,0:23:40.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}:\N Kid, Conan, and the Ryoma Treasure Illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.69,0:23:40.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kid, Conan, and the Ryoma Treasure Illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.15,0:23:42.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Step right this way! Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.83,0:23:45.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.00,0:23:46.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.32,0:23:48.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't miss the illusion!
